body: Trump thinks way too highly of himself. I've heard his comments and he basically sees himself as perfect and not a mortal. This is dangerous because it leads to thinking you can't ever be wrong. I don't think Trump is actually an authoritarian at heart but his ego sometimes allows him to make controlling decisions because he thinks of himself as infallible. And somehow his attitude fools a lot of otherwise smart people, and they end up worshiping him and become utterly blind to his mistakes.
